This is a custom, unique character created by Anna Danilov. Everyone in childhood had a favorite toy, our little hero. Most often it was a bear. We remember this bear as gentle and kind. Our childhood was the same, carefree and cheerful. But with age, the world changes, we grow up and become responsible for our life and future. The world around us ceases to be what it seemed in childhood. Therefore, "our bear" is changing in our eyes. The idea of ​​this picture is that the sweet bear has become rougher in real conditions. Each of us has our own dreams, but someone or something can stop us. Therefore, the yellow lines “caution” are obstacles. Money is always a trend in the modern world. If you want to achieve success, be able to fully provide your life with everything you need, no one can stop you, only yourself. The black paper shred filler is someone else's opinion. Stop paying attention to what others say.

Recently I realized that I completely forgot about the time for myself. More precisely, I pushed it into the background, put it in a drawer and forgot. But you can't do that. Work at home, work in the studio. Work. Work. Work. Thoughts are busy with new projects, drawings, I started online education. It's all great, but it's time to remember about yourself, about what I love. I decided to conduct a challenge for myself, in several stages, there will be 3 of them. I want to regain my previous form, which I had a few years ago. And then start building a new one, which one I haven’t decided yet. I'll choose the accent later. Each stage will consist of 3 different months. Each month has its own program. I came up with this program many years ago and it works. Let's see how it will be now. Much has changed in the way of life, there is no time even for sleep. But if you don't try, you won't know. Today was the second day of the first stage and I'm happy. Further more.

This picture is from my collection
 «Faith. Love. Freedom», which I created piece by piece. It carries great meaning. If you look at it carefully, you will see an imitation of different elements. But the most important thing is that it has life. There is water and a real plant that represents life. The idea for the painting came about quite by accident, like all the ideas that come to me at different moments of my life. Once I was in the shower and closing my eyes, when I realized how fortunate we are to have water. I can take a shower and not think that this water will run out, while people in some countries dream of taking at least one sip of water. And why is someone born with the opportunity to have everything, while someone else struggles to survive? Therefore, this picture carries a huge meaning. Our planet consists of layers of the globe, with different surfaces and natural elements. Therefore, I created an imitation of layers, an imitation of stone and water. And most importantly, LIFE. The wooden panels represent layers, and the surface on them is stone. The liquid glass gives an imitation of water, which also flows down the wall of the back panel. Water is life, and it never stands still. The moss that is on the back panel and visible through the slots in the main panel is the beginning of life. Fresh flowers in a glass vessel with water - HERE IS LIFE! It is real and beautiful! Even a small blade of grass or a small flower can break through a stone and grow if it believes in itself. Therefore, the imitation of slots in the panel is a symbol of possibility, the ability to live, grow, and create the world you want. Believe in yourself, and everything will work out. You are unique, strong, smart, alive, and you deserve everything!

Each painting has its own story. It can be born long ago and come true in an instant. Each picture absorbs energy, feelings, emotions, love of the creator. My feelings when painting this picture are like zen that has penetrated my body and soul. Even creating it, I experienced the emotions and moments of not only my life, but also the life of this Leo.  His gaze penetrates the soul, it reads courage, kindness, wisdom, care that penetrates the heart. I have never experienced so many feelings while creating paintings. But this Leo turned a lot in my life and in my mind. @gaysina_anna @ani.art.miami

Sometimes I think, what would have happened if I had not stopped painting 8 years ago? How would my life be? What would I do now? How would I live now? But I'm sure of one thing, I'm grateful for where I am now! I am grateful for the experience, I am grateful for the lessons of life. I am glad to all those people whom I met and let go of those whose path is not similar to mine. I am grateful for every second. What matters is what I want now and where I want to go, who I want to become, what I want to achieve. We ourselves create our world, the main thing is to choose a path and start improving ourselves by creating this world. Trust your inner voice because the most important person in your life is you. Your closest friend is yourself! Live this life brightly, live this life the way you want!

I want to tell you a little story. Today my daughter (she is 5 years old) came up to me and said: “Mom, when I grow up, I will be an artist like you!” To which I replied: “You can be an artist now and much better than me. Why not?". The emotions on her face were so sincere and pure, this joy and smile at the same time is the best thing to see. I reminded her of how the last time we were at the Art Basel, we saw a very talented boy, he was 10 years old at that time. This inspired her, because she is only 5 years old, but she already wants to become a talented artist. She asked me to create an Instagram page for her (of course I will manage it), but she wants to try it and I will gladly support her. Who other than her parents, the closest people in her life, can help realize her ideas and start this interesting path. Yes, maybe now her soul is asking for it, maybe in the future she will want to be someone else. But at the moment when her heart is drawn to art, I will do my best to convey to her my knowledge, my experience and my support to the maximum extent. And I will be sincerely glad if she is a much more talented and successful artist than me. "I love you very much, my sunshine, I'm always there." Thanks to everyone who read this mini story to the end, more wonderful works and Ariana’s new path you can see on her page @ari.art.miami 💕
P.S. ~She also came up with the name, ARI.ART. Inspired by my ANI.ART. I am not against that~ 😉 Love U

I love painting at night. When it’s busy all day outside, everyone has work, the sounds of cars, birds singing, the sound of the ocean waves, the summer wind... this is also a kind of certain vibe. I love being in my studio, but when the evening comes and it’s time to go home, I switch to night mode. Many people go to restaurants in the evenings, to parties, but I like to come to my home studio, to my home art space, take a pencil, a canvas and create a new art piece. Today I heard a song that entered my soul. And I thought, why not go to the balcony? The perfect tandem. Night, music in headphones, canvas, night city. Fascinating... Stars... Isn’t it wonderful?

“FAITH.LOVE.FREEDOM”
This picture is from my collection «Faith. Love. Freedom», which I created piece by piece. It carries great meaning. If you look at it carefully, you will see an imitation of different elements. But the most important thing is that it has life. There is water and a real plant that represents life. The idea for the painting came about quite by accident, like all the ideas that come to me at different moments of my life. Once I was in the shower and closing my eyes, when I realized how fortunate we are to have water. I can take a shower and not think that this water will run out, while people in some countries dream of taking at least one sip of water. And why is someone born with the opportunity to have everything, while someone else struggles to survive? Therefore, this picture carries a huge meaning. Our planet consists of layers of the globe, with different surfaces and natural elements. Therefore, I created an imitation of layers, an imitation of stone and water. And most importantly, LIFE. The wooden panels represent layers, and the surface on them is stone. The liquid glass gives an imitation of water, which also flows down the wall of the back panel. Water is life, and it never stands still. The moss that is on the back panel and visible through the slots in the main panel is the beginning of life. Fresh flowers in a glass vessel with water - HERE IS LIFE! It is real and beautiful! Even a small blade of grass or a small flower can break through a stone and grow if it believes in itself. Therefore, the imitation of slots in the panel is a symbol of possibility, the ability to live, grow, and create the world you want. Believe in yourself, and everything will work out. You are unique, strong, smart, alive, and you deserve everything!

I am grateful to those people who were able to see what others could not see. This is a custom, unique character created by Anna Danilov. Everyone in childhood had a favorite toy, our little hero. Most often it was a bear. We remember this bear as gentle and kind. Our childhood was the same, carefree and cheerful. But with age, the world changes, we grow up and become responsible for our life and future. The world around us ceases to be what it seemed in childhood. Therefore, "our bear" is changing in our eyes. The idea of ​​this picture is that the sweet bear has become rougher in real conditions. Each of us has our own dreams, but someone or something can stop us. Therefore, the yellow lines “caution” are obstacles. Money is always a trend in the modern world. If you want to achieve success, be able to fully provide your life with everything you need, no one can stop you, only yourself. The black paper shred filler is someone else's opinion. Stop paying attention to what others say.
